The essential requirements for a HPB center to deliver high quality outcomes.
We propose criteria for essential requirements for a HPB center to deliver high quality outcomes, with the concept of "center of reference" limited to actual, in opposition to virtual, centers. LAY SUMMARY: After a comprehensive literature review and a large international survey, we present the requirements for HPB center to deliver quality outcomes. The worldwide survey showed that there is a need for "re-designing" HPB centers, as only one third of surveyed centers meet most of the criteria.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Therapeutic advances in alcohol-associated hepatitis. 
Meanwhile, the broader medical field has seen a transformation in care paradigms based on emerging digital technologies. This review focuses on breakthroughs in our understanding of AH and how these breakthroughs are leading to new paradigms for biomarker discovery, clinical trial activity, and care models for patients. It portends a future in which multimodal data from genetic, radiomic, histologic, and environmental sources can be integrated and synthesised to generate personalised biomarkers and therapies for patients with AH.
